      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "You are absolutely right to be concerned about the operational impact, but downgrading a \"Critical\" SQL injection risk during peak season creates an existential threat to customer trust and regulatory compliance. A post-click pump or successful lateral movement could result in massive financial losses far exceeding any cost of a temporary outage, plus the reputational damage could take months to recover. Since the scan indicates a high likelihood of exploit, the only safe recommendation is to proceed with the emergency maintenance window immediately to isolate the vulnerability, even if it requires strong communication with stakeholders regarding the urgent security necessity.",
